	<div class="the-comment" id="comment-1475693">

		<div class="comment-meta">

			<span class="comment-author">Jake Lane</span>
			<span class="comment-link">
				<a href="#comment-1475693" title="Comment Permalink">
					<span class="comment-date">February 5, 2014</span>
					<span class="comment-middot">&middot;</span>
					<span class="comment-time">10:03 am</span>
				</a>
			</span>
		</div>
		<div class="comment-content" style="display:block;">

			<p>Raising the minimum wage and drastically reforming the healthcare system are great ways to improve daily life as well as strengthen the economy. With socialized medicine the deficit will be decreased, standard of living will go up, and healthcare will not be the acquisitive business that it has developed into. Despite this, many on the right wing label these as &#8220;Liberal&#8221; or even &#8220;Socialist&#8221; ideas. They also said the same thing when F.D.R. introduced programs that we could not imagine living without today such as social security, the Fair Labor and Standards Act, and the Home Owners Loan Act. We need to keep pushing progressive ideas or else this income gap will grow like it did in the early 1900s. We will continue falling behind the rest of the world if we do not change.</p>

		</div>
